               <head>Treatise comparing Islamic and Hindu mysticism</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Rawz̤at al-maʿārif by Bhayyah Jīvan Rām</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1023-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7092">Bhayyah Jīvan Rām</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22188">Rawz̤at al-maʿārif</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara urd">Persian, Arabic, and Urdu</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise comparing Islamic mystical thought with aspects of Hindu theology, by <persName key="person_f7092" role="aut">Bhayyah Jīvan Rām-jīv</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work comprises of eight chapters based on the hast bihisht division of heaven. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 111r): completed by <persName key="person_f7107" role="scr">Dayā Rām</persName> at the farkhandah bunyād <placeName>Ḥaydarābād</placeName>, 7 Rajab 1140/18 February 1728. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
